Expanded service
› A new agreement between Northwest Airlines and
Alaska Airlines covers 37 cities throughout the U.S.,
Canada, Mexico, the Caribbean, Asia and Europe,
with over 280 flights daily effective 10/29/95.
Our new coordinated system offers one-stop
check-in; boarding passes, seat assignments and
automated baggage tags to final destination,
plus automatic WorldPerks® mileage credits.
Bonus Miles
• Earn 500 WorldPerks Bonus Miles on each qualifying
flight segment on Alaska Airlines, Horizon Air or
Northwest designated flights (7000-7999), plus
Minneapolis/St. Paul-Anchorage daily nonstop flight
between October 29, 1995 and January 31, 1996.
Enhanced benefits to WorldPerks members
v WorldPerks members also earn a minimum of
500 WorldPerks miles per flight segment on
Alaska Airlines. Preferred members are eligible
for an additional 25% credit and Gold members
receive a 100% bonus.
For reservations, and complete details on
WorldPerks Program and Bonus Miles, call your
travel professional or Northwest Airlines at
1-800-225-2525.
